"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-lady-gaga-brings-cabaret-to-olympics-opening-ceremony-on-paris-river-seine\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Published\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:38 AM  Updated\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 06:24 AM  PARIS - French President Emmanuel Macron declared the Olympic Games open on July 26 after a soaking wet ceremony in which athletes were cheered by the crowd along the Seine, dancers took to the roofs of Paris and Lady Gaga sang a French cabaret song.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2432829834291114e-16, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3790543764192226e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.17760228651066e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s three-time Olympic gold medallists Marie-Jose Perec and Teddy Riner then lit the Olympic cauldron, suspended on a hot-air balloon, before Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Celine Dion sang Edith Piaf\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Hymn To Love, in her first public performance in years, drawing huge cheers from the crowd.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999295142, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}, {\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A fleet of barges took the competitors on a 6km stretch of the river alongside some of the French capital\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most famous landmarks, as performers recreated some of the sports to be showcased in the Games on floating platforms.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the first time that an opening ceremony has taken place outside a stadium, adding to the headaches for a vast security operation, just hours aftera sabotage attack on the high-speed TGV rail networkcaused travel chaos across France.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TGV\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\"}, {\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999563443, \"rank\": 3.265389781670281e-11, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI invite everybody: dream with us.\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like the Olympic athletes, be inspired with the joy that only sport can give us.\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us celebrate this Olympic spirit of living in peace,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d International Olympics Committee president Thomas Bach said, as the ceremony came to an end at the foot of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1534, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 10,500 athletes will compete at the Olympics, 100 years since Paris last staged the Games.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.17760228651066e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition started on July 24 and the first of the 329 gold medals will be awarded on July 27.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the show started four hours earlier, a giant plume of blue, white and red smoke, resembling the French flag, was sent high above a bridge over the Seine as part of a show that included many postcard-like depictions of France, including a huge cancan line performed by Moulin Rouge dancers on the banks.\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1915, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3790543764192226e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999563443, \"rank\": 3.265389781670281e-11, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.350916049945488e-37, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more modern image of the country was on display when French-Malian pop star Aya Nakamura, the most-listened to French female singer in the world, sang some of her biggest hits, accompanied by the French Republican Guard\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s army choir.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 2236, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_First_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999999105234605, \"rank\": 8.884250333312895e-08, \"text\": \"French Republican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_First_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_First_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nakamura\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s performance drew some of the ceremony\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s biggest cheers.\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rumours of her inclusion had sparked a row over French identity, with supporters saying said she represented the vibrancy of modern-day France while her detractors saying her music owes more to foreign influences than French.\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2570, \"end\": 2576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999563443, \"rank\": 3.265389781670281e-11, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2652, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the celebration of French culture, fashion and history was warmly cheered by many of the 300,000 spectators lining the river, hundreds were seen leaving early as the rain fell.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s athletes aboard a boat in the floating parade on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt was good other than the rain, it was nice, it was different, instead of being in a stadium being on the river, so that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s always a good thing - interesting, unique,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Avid Pureval, 34, who came to the Games from Ohio.\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3122, \"end\": 3126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\", \"score\": 0.99999994148766, \"rank\": 3.948999599234981e-08, \"text\": \"Avid\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avid_Technology\"}, {\"begin\": 3167, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\", \"score\": 0.7791687904888366, \"rank\": 0.28341896135199696, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOnce you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re wet, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fine,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said.\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, he was heading back to his hotel after the French boat passed, long before the ceremony ended.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3271, \"end\": 3277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt would have been better with sun,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Josephine, from Paris, sitting beside her nine-year-old daughter and who paid \\u00e2\\u0082\\u00ac1,600 (S$2,300) for her seat.\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3387, \"end\": 3392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.17760228651066e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes of Germany, Algeria, Albania and Afghanistan pass Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099  Eiffel Tower aboard a boat, in the Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.781563738283407, \"rank\": 0.2793160507869902, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 3504, \"end\": 3511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9998520847668693, \"rank\": 0.0001478168418719474, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3513, \"end\": 3520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albania\", \"score\": 0.9999997651098331, \"rank\": 2.2461910165141323e-07, \"text\": \"Albania\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albania\"}, {\"begin\": 3525, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999776299606421, \"rank\": 2.236892935387817e-05, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 3552, \"end\": 3564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9870590557418948e-54, \"text\": \"Eiffel Tower\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  With many world leaders and VIPs present, the ceremony was protected by snipers on rooftops.\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s riverbed was swept for bombs, and Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 airspace was closed.\", \"from\": 3725, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 45,000 police and thousands of soldiers were deployed in a huge security operation in Paris for the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3895, \"end\": 3900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.17760228651066e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Armed police patrolled along the river in inflatable boats as the armada made its passage along the Seine.\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 4026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4020, \"end\": 4025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3790543764192226e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A mix of French and international stars, including soccer great Zinedine Zidane, 14-times French Open champion Rafa Nadal, 23-times Grand Slam champion Serena Williams and three paralympic athletes were among the last torchbearers before the cauldron was lit.\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4037, \"end\": 4043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4092, \"end\": 4107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 4139, \"end\": 4149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafa Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 4180, \"end\": 4195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will blaze until the closing ceremony on Aug 11.\", \"from\": 4289, \"to\": 4340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the start of the parade, applause erupted for the Greek boat - the first delegation, by tradition - and there were even bigger cheers for the boat that followed, carrying the refugees\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 team.\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4395, \"end\": 4400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9920224525200858, \"rank\": 0.007726649778437497, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French, US and Ukrainian delegations also got loud cheers.\", \"from\": 4538, \"to\": 4600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4542, \"end\": 4548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9973145484235338, \"rank\": 0.0025206461430411103, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4550, \"end\": 4552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9947465621767105, \"rank\": 0.005280025036329231, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4557, \"end\": 4566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9993759384293144, \"rank\": 0.0006232505725287164, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two most decorated athletes in the Games\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history, Michael Phelps and Martin Fourcade, unveiled the gold, silver and bronze medals.\", \"from\": 4602, \"to\": 4739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4659, \"end\": 4673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.555477853431678e-37, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627